## Context
The §3.1 worked transaction (World Bank IBRD + Clean Technology Fund, Turkiye
TPTS project P508354) already names actors, sites, instruments, rates and dates.
The Vannes notes ask for the one-to-one mapping from that case to the four
controversies to be made explicit in the text. Tracker: 0141.

## Relevant passages
- `content/manuscript.qmd` §3.1 — the Turkiye worked transaction and the four
  controversies (additionality; value + credibility; attribution).
- `docs/notes-vannes-2026-07.md` §5.

## Actions
1. Map the case to each controversy explicitly:
   - additionality — is it a climate project? ("electrons have no colour"; the WB
     financed grids long before Rio)
   - value + credibility — how much finance is really in this project?
   - attribution — the OECD/Oxfam duel over who counts it.
2. Keep the §3.1 concreteness (project ID, rates, dates); add the mapping as
   connective tissue, not a new table.

## Test (prose ratchet)
- Negative guard only; keep the existing concrete figures traceable.

## Exit criteria
- [ ] §3.1 case mapped one-to-one to the four controversies in prose
- [ ] Cover-letter traceability rows (R2.g2/R2.34) updated with §ref + commit SHA
